What you need to know:

Well-connected ‘tenderprenuers’ were trotting around town carrying commitment letters running into billions of shillings.The last time I saw an example of this level of impunity and corruption in government procurement was in the late 1980s.It is the taxpayer who is now expected to pay a whopping Sh2.9 billion to compensate ‘stakeholders’ who were mobilised by Kemsa.